reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing Mini Projector.
reviews.reviewText: I bought this projector to use for outside movie nights with my family. When I saw this mini projector I was somewhat hesitant to buy it because it was listed so cheap. You always think if you buy cheap you get cheap but this is not thE case.When I got the projector it came with everything to set it up and use it right out of the box. I tried every input type to ensure it worked. I was able to watch a movie off a flash drive, I plugged a Kindle Fire stick into it, I’ve played with my switch and my xBox One on it. It has been an amazing little machine.Indoors quality is really good. You do need a darkened room but I could low amounts of light in the right circumstances doesn’t feminist the quality a whole lot but you’re not going to use the projector in a lit room anyway. So far I’ve been able to project up to the specified largest screen size and found that the projector works well. It does become a little pixelated at the largest projection rate but for what I paid for this projector it was not an issue I would complain about.My living room television went out and I’m currently using this projector in its place until my television gets repaired. I worried at fist about extended use, wondering if it would over heat, but after several weeks of use and 1 full 10-12 hours running in 1 day I find this little projector is worth the purchase price.As you can see in the photos I have my mini projector mounted on a camera tripod, which easily screws into the leveler screw on the bottom front of the projector. I use a JBL Flip 4 speaker or a large portable Karaoke speaker I’ve had for a while.If you’re looking for a mini projector for outdoors fun or even as a gaming projector this one is a great investment. I have had 0 issues with this projector and I’m looking forward to seeing how long the projector lamp will last before needing to be replaced.Photo one is the projector in my wife’s school office at home. Screen size comparable to 60” television.Photo two is outside projected on a cinder block wall that has not been prepped or painted for projection. Screen size comparable to 110” television.Photo 3 is in my living room projected onto the wall where my revision is usually mounted. At this location I did have to add some blackout curtains to block more light. Screen size comparable to 80” television.As you can see the picture is really clear in each photo.Buy this projector and have loads of fun with your family and friends.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: We are new to the projector world. We enclosed our back porch and had music, but felt that tv was missing. After looking at tons of projectors We decided on this one. It wasn't super pricey and the reviews were good for it. It plays well and clear, we did a movie night it was AWESOME!!!! I started before it got dark (the sun was in) and a tan curtain was our screen and it was like sitting inside watching TV. You do have to buy the cord to connect to your phone to stream from your phone, it was only $13-$14 bucks. Make sure you get the right one. I have a Droid. It's simple to operate once I got the hang and I am very pleased. The reviews also said the volume isn't good. I kinda agree, if it's a couple people (and quiet) it's fine, for larger crowds you might need that "UMPH"!! I had a small Bluetooth speaker that I connected ( to my phone) for that extra "boost" and that was just great. I recommend this projector 100%.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good little projector!
reviews.reviewText: Ive had this product for over a year now and its never failed to be great for me and my fiance.This projector is super easy to set up and use, we usually keep a Roku plugged into one of the USB ports and an HDMI so anytime we turn on the projector the Roku powers up as well.Ill go over some of the main things I've noticed from this projector and be as honest as i can.The model i have is slightly older than the model being shown now, but i imagine not a ton has changed.Picture:This projector has good quality for its price. We had it set up so it displayed on a wall about 16 feet away and the quality is what you would expect from a projector. Its really only noticeable if youre close to the wall/screen. I will say the brightness is tough to see during the day, but thats with most projectors.Sound:This is a small projector, so it has small speakers. They dont have much bass, but in general for shows its done well. I would recommenrd some external speakers plugged in to really give it the kick it needs.Mounting:This projector cant be mounted unless you get creative. It does NOT have the "standard" projector mounting holes. That being said, if youre sitting it on a shelf or table, theres a screw/stand you can use to adjust the angle, which is useful. This projector does come with several options for displaying (upside down, flipped, etc..) for any way you could want it to project. We tied (with some paracord) ours to a projector mount that screwed into the ceiling and its stable enough to not wobble or fall and it imitates a 65in tv in our bedroom.To summarize, its a good projector. Its light and super portable, it had good quality and good speakers. If youre setting up an in-home theater this isnt for you. But for college students in a dorm or apartment, or really anybody not wanting to spend a bunch of money on a large TV that's hard to transport, this is a GREAT solution.Lastly i have to mention customer support. We lost the remote to ours during a move and getting up to turn it on/off, adjust volume. etc.. was horrible. I emailed Hompow customer service and after verifying my purchase they immediately sent me a replacement remote and they were delightful during the whole process. Supplying me with the tracking number for the package and following up to make sure I received it and it works.Trust me you skepitcal projector shopper, you cant go wrong with this one. Hompow is doing it right.
